    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-03-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-03-17T17:50:01Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) make permanent the tax deduction for qualified tuition and related expenses; (2) increase the maximum amount of such deduction to $5,000 and repeal provisions requiring a phaseout of the deduction based on adjusted gross income; and (3) allow grandparents to claim a deduction for the tuition and related expenses of their grandchildren. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to modify and make permanent the deduction for qualified tuition and related expenses.</title>
